<h4>MOTOR SYSTEM EXAMINATION</h4>
<h5>Inspection:</h5>
<ul>
<li>Overall Appearance: <em>(e.g., Posture, any obvious deformities)</em></li>
<li>Muscle Bulk: <em>(e.g., Normal, Atrophy - specify L/R, Hypertrophy -
          specify L/R)</em></li>
<li>Muscle Tone (Passive ROM):
        <ul>
<li>Upper Limbs: <em>(Normal, Hypotonic/Flaccid, Hypertonic -
              Spastic/Rigid)</em> - Left / Right</li>
<li>Lower Limbs: <em>(Normal, Hypotonic/Flaccid, Hypertonic -
              Spastic/Rigid)</em> - Left / Right</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Involuntary Movements: <em>(None, Tremor - rest/intention,
          Fasciculations, Chorea, etc. - specify L/R &amp; characteristics)</em></li>
</ul>
<h5>Motor Strength (MRC Scale: 0-5):</h5>
<p><em>Scale: 0=No contraction, 1=Flicker, 2=Movement with gravity
        eliminated, 3=Movement against gravity, 4=Movement against some
        resistance, 5=Normal power</em></p>
