<h3>CEREBELLAR EXAMINATION</h3>
<iframe src="Cerebellar%20ataxia%20CASE%20SHEET.html"></iframe>
<p><br/>
</p>
<details>
<summary>EXPAND EXAMINATION: SUSPECTED MENINGITIS</summary>
<br/>
<div class="video-container"> <iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="864" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/A4iPHEGEoTs" title="Meningitis by Dr Ankur #GotAspirEd" width="1520"></iframe> </div>
<p><em>(<b>Prerequisites:</b> Doctor states: "I assume I've taken all the
          universal precautions" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=2s">Video
            0:02-0:04</a>). Ensure patient privacy and obtain consent where
          applicable throughout the examination.)</em></p>
<p><strong>PATIENT STATUS:</strong> Drowsy, responsive to voice with
        moans, appears uncomfortable.</p>
<h4>A. INTRODUCTION &amp; INITIAL ASSESSMENT</h4>
<ul>
<li>Attempt to rouse patient and introduce self: "Hello? Hello, my name
          is Dr. Ankur, one of the doctors in the department. May I confirm your
          name please?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=4s">Video
            0:04-0:11</a>). Patient moans.</li>
<li>Check patient responsiveness: "Hello, are you okay?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=14s">Video
            0:14-0:15</a>). Patient moans.</li>
<li>Identify patient: Checks wristband. "John." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=18s">Video
            0:18-0:21</a>).</li>
<li>Further questioning: "Hello John, how are you? Is anything bothering
          you? Are you in pain, John?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=22s">Video
            0:22-0:33</a>). Patient moans.</li>
</ul>
<h4>B. PAIN MANAGEMENT &amp; ENVIRONMENTAL COMFORT</h4>
<ul>
<li>Request for analgesia: "Examiner, I would like to give painkiller to
          my patient after ruling out all the allergies and contraindications."
          (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=34s">Video
            0:34-0:39</a>). Examiner: "Assume Dr. you have given painkiller." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=40s">Video
            0:40-0:41</a>).</li>
<li>Re-assess post-analgesia: "John, I have given you painkiller. Are
          you fine now? Could you please put your hands down on your side?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=43s">Video
            0:43-0:50</a>). Patient moans.</li>
<li>Inquire about photophobia: "Is anything else bothering you? John, is
          light bothering you?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=52s">Video
            0:52-0:59</a>). Patient moans.</li>
<li>Request to dim lights: "Examiner, I would like to dim the light for
          my patient." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=61s">Video
            1:01-1:02</a>). Examiner: "Assume." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=63s">Video
            1:03</a>).</li>
<li>Re-assess post-dimming lights: "John, I have given you painkiller, I
          have dimmed the light for you. Are you fine now? Could you please put
          your hands on your side?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=65s">Video
            1:05-1:14</a>). Patient moans.</li>
<li>Assist patient with arm positioning: "Let me help you, John." (Moves
          patient's arms to their sides). "I'm sorry, I'm sorry." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=75s">Video
            1:15-1:21</a>).</li>
</ul>
<h4>C. VITAL SIGNS &amp; GLASGOW COMA SCALE (GCS) ASSESSMENT</h4>
<ul>
<li>Review vital signs chart: "Let me see your vitals." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=83s">Video
            1:23-1:24</a>).
          <ul>
<li>RRe: 12-20. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=85s">Video
                1:25-1:27</a>)</li>
<li>SpO2: 94-95%. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=87s">Video
                1:27-1:30</a>)</li>
<li>Temp: 38°C. "My patient has got temperature." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=91s">Video
                1:31-1:33</a>)</li>
<li>BP: 120/80 mmHg. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=94s">Video
                1:34-1:36</a>)</li>
<li>Pulse: 90 bpm. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=96s">Video
                1:36-1:38</a>)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>GCS Assessment:</strong> "John, now I'd like to check your
          conscious level." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=101s">Video
            1:41-1:43</a>)
          <ul>
<li><strong>Eye Opening (E):</strong> "Could you please open your
              eyes and keep them open for me?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=105s">Video
                1:45-1:47</a>). Patient tries but cannot keep eyes open. </li>
<ul>
<li>Doctor later <b>scores </b>this as 3. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=155s">Video
                  2:35-2:39</a>)</li>
</ul>
<li><strong>Verbal Response (V):</strong> "John, could you please
              tell me where we are now?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=113s">Video
                1:53-1:54</a>). Patient makes incomprehensible sounds. </li>
<ul>
<li>Doctor later <b>scores </b>this as 2. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=160s">Video
                  2:40-2:46</a>)</li>
</ul>
<li><strong>Motor Response (M):</strong>
<ul>
<li>To command: "Could you please raise your right arm for me,
                  John?... Could you please raise your left arm for me?... Could
                  you please raise your right leg for me?... Could you please
                  raise your left leg for me?... Could you please stick out your
                  tongue?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=122s">Video
                    2:02-2:23</a>). No response to commands.</li>
<li>To pain (thumb squeeze): "Now I'm going to squeeze your
                  thumb." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=145s">Video
                    2:25-2:26</a>). Patient shows flexion withdrawal. </li>
<li>Doctor later <b>scores </b>this as 4. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=171s">Video
                    2:51-2:56</a>)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Total GCS Score:</strong> 3 (Eyes) + 2 (Verbal) + 4
              (Motor) = 9/15. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=177s">Video
                2:57-3:02</a>)</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h4>D. MENINGEAL IRRITATION SIGNS</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Neck Stiffness &amp; Brudzinski's Sign:</strong> "Could you
          please bring your chin towards your chest? Let me help you, John."
          (Passively flexes neck). Patient shows resistance and involuntary
          flexion of hips and knees. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=187s">Video
            3:07-3:14</a>). "My patient has got neck stiffness and Brudzinski's
          sign is positive." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=196s">Video
            3:16-3:19</a>).</li>
<li><strong>Kernig's Sign:</strong> "John, now I'm going to touch your
          leg. Please relax." (Flexes hip and knee to 90 degrees, then attempts
          to extend the knee). Patient shows resistance and pain. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=200s">Video
            3:20-3:30</a>). "My patient has got Kernig's sign positive." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=212s">Video
            3:32-3:34</a>).</li>
</ul>
<h4>E. RASH EXAMINATION</h4>
<ul>
<li>Expose patient: "Okay John, now I would like to expose you so that I
          can examine you, I can check your rashes. Don't worry, I have a
          chaperone with me throughout my examination to ensure your privacy.
          May I proceed John?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=215s">Video
            3:35-3:46</a>). Examiner: "Assume Dr." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=226s">Video
            3:46-3:47</a>).</li>
<li>Inspect for rash: "I'm looking for the rash on the chest, neck,
          axilla, behind the ear." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=232s">Video
            3:52-4:05</a>). Examiner: "Doctor, assume there is a rash on the
          chest." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=245s">Video
            4:05-4:07</a>).</li>
<li><strong>Glass Test (Tumbler Test):</strong> "I'd like to do glass
          test." (Simulates pressing a glass against the rash). (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=251s">Video
            4:11-4:15</a>). "The rash is non-blanching." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=256s">Video
            4:16-4:18</a>).</li>
<li>Cover patient: "Okay John, now I would like to cover you back to
          prevent hypothermia." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=259s">Video
            4:19-4:22</a>).</li>
</ul>
<h4>F. CONCLUSION &amp; DISCUSSION WITH EXAMINER</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Examiner: "What is your diagnosis,
          Doctor?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=264s">Video
            4:24-4:26</a>). Doctor: "Examiner, I am suspecting my patient has
          got meningitis." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=266s">Video
            4:26-4:29</a>).</li>
<li><strong>Reasoning for Diagnosis:</strong> Examiner: "Why do you
          think so?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=270s">Video
            4:30</a>). Doctor explains based on headache, photophobia, fever
          (38°C), positive Kernig's and Brudzinski's signs, neck stiffness,
          and non-blanching rash on the chest. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=271s">Video
            4:31-4:50</a>).</li>
<li><strong>Management Plan:</strong> Examiner: "What do you want to do
          for your patient?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=290s">Video
            4:50-4:51</a>). Doctor outlines:
          <ul>
<li>Admit patient.</li>
<li>Provide adequate analgesia.</li>
<li>Isolate patient.</li>
<li>Inform seniors.</li>
<li>Further investigations: Routine blood tests (LFTs, KFTs, FBC),
              blood culture.</li>
<li>Consider CT scan to rule out contraindications for lumbar
              puncture.</li>
<li>Perform lumbar puncture.</li>
<li>Administer antibiotics (according to hospital protocol).</li>
<li>Administer antipyretics (e.g., paracetamol) for fever.</li>
<li>Trace contacts and provide prophylactic antibiotics.</li>
<li>Consider IV fluids and oxygen. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=292s">Video
                4:52-5:39</a>)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Differential Diagnoses:</strong> Examiner: "Doctor, what are
          your differentials?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=340s">Video
            5:40-5:41</a>). Doctor: "Subarachnoid hemorrhage, tension headache,
          cluster headache, or migraine." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=342s">Video
            5:42-5:51</a>).</li>
<li>Examiner concludes: "Okay, thank you Doctor." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A4iPHEGEoTs&t=352s">Video
            5:52-5:53</a>).</li>
</ul>
</details>
